Document: Joint2D
Path: godot/classes/class_joint2d.rst
Summary: Properties and member variables of the Joint2D class in Godot Engine.

bias (float): 0.0. Controls how fast the joint pulls bodies back to their original position when they move in different directions. Lower values allow more movement. Uses ProjectSettings.physics/2d/solver/default_constraint_bias when set to 0. Set via set_bias(value: float), get via get_bias().

disable_collision (bool): true. If enabled, the two connected bodies do not collide with each other. Set via set_exclude_nodes_from_collision(value: bool), get via get_exclude_nodes_from_collision().

node_a (NodePath): NodePath(""). Path to the first physics body (A) attached to the joint. Must inherit PhysicsBody2D. Set via set_node_a(value: NodePath), get via get_node_a().

node_b (NodePath): NodePath(""). Path to the second physics body (B) attached to the joint. Must inherit PhysicsBody2D. Set via set_node_b(value: NodePath), get via get_node_b().
---CHUNK---
